## R1
WHEN the user runs `./init.sh`, the system MUST print "Hello, Harness!"
to stdout and exit with code 0.

## R2
WHEN the user runs `./init.sh --name <name>`, the system MUST print
"Hello, <name>!" instead of the default greeting.

## R3
IF `./init.sh` is invoked with `--help`, the system MUST print usage
information listing all available flags.

## R4
WHILE the `--name` flag is missing, the system MUST use the default
greeting "Hello, Harness!".
